===Etymology===
{{term|hello|Hello|lang=en}} (first attested in 1833), from {{term|holla|lang=en}}, {{term|hollo|lang=en}} (attested 1588). This variant of {{term|hallo|lang=en}} is often credited to [[w:Thomas Edison|Thomas Edison]] as a coinage for telephone use, but its appearance in print predates the invention of the telephone by several decades.

Possibly from the {{etyl|goh|en}} and {{etyl|osx|en}} verb {{term|halon|lang=goh}}, {{term|holon||to bring something, to gather|lang=goh}}, akin to {{etyl|en|-}} {{term|hale|lang=en}} or {{term|hail|lang=en}}.

